    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest little car that\u2019s priced for someone who wants affordable wheels or a solid project to tinker with. It\u2019s not perfect and shows its age, but it still has plenty of potential for the right buyer. If you\u2019re after something budget-friendly and straightforward, this could be a great fit. Come have a look and see if it\u2019s the one for you.",
      "price": 4900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver/project with strong mechanical character and plenty of upside. Engine starts, runs, and pulls with good torque, and the drivetrain feels like a great foundation for someone who appreciates a car with honest wear instead of hidden surprises. Not a showroom piece, but a straightforward car with usable road manners, a serviceable chassis, and the kind of simple, fix-as-you-go ownership that makes sense for a commuter, backup vehicle, or weekend tinkering platform. If you want an affordable car with real potential and no pretensions, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 6900.0,
